title: Fish Balls In Tomato-basil Sauce
summary: Fish Balls In Tomato-basil Sauce requires approximately 1 hour from start to finish. This dairy free and pescatarian recipe serves 1 and costs $11.65 per serving. One serving contains 1394 calories, 116g of protein, and 76g of fat. If you have tarragon, bread, canolan oil, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the eggs you could follow this main course with the Rose Levy Beranbaum's Chocolate Tomato Cake with Mystery Ganache as a dessert. It works well as a main course. 1 person were impressed by this recipe. It is brought to you by Recipezaar. Overall, this recipe earns an outstanding spoonacular score of 84%. Try Mozzarella Stuffed Chicken Sausage Balls, Tomato-Basil Sauce, Cacio e Pepe Potatoes and Roast Broccolini, Tomato-Basil Baked Fish, and Feta Tomato-Basil Fish for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Fish works really well with Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. The La Fiera Pinot Grigio with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 7 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: La Fiera Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: This wine has a light straw color with green tints. It has a light floral and fruity bouquet featuring apples and pears. The palate is bright, fresh and dry showing nice balance and a lingering acidity perfect for a variety of lighter cuisine.Blend: 100% Pinot Grigio

instructions: In a food processor, process all of the fish ball ingredients except for the fish/flour/oil. Add in the fish and mix thoroughly.Mold the fish mixture into balls the size and shape of an egg (if the mixture doesn't cooperate and falls apart, you may want to mix in an egg to help it bind together). Dredge the balls in the flour.Heat the oil in a skillet, add the fish and brown on all sides (approximately 2-3 minutes). Place them in a greased baking dish. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.In a food processor, grind all the sauce ingredients into a smooth paste. Pour it over the fish balls, and bake for approximately 30-35 minutes.Can be served chilled, at room temperature or hot.
